00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:04.582
And so I see so much lack. I see so many people believing for something.

00:25:04.583 --> 00:25:25.519
And as I was listening to them at this conference believing for, I mean, it was like mega money, like more money than is like, to me, the money that they need for this project, I thought, 'Lord, how do we get that?'It shouldn't be that the body of Christ is struggling for this.

00:25:25.520 --> 00:25:30.124
There should be a million surplus because we're doing what you asked us to do.

00:25:30.125 --> 00:25:32.775
Do you see what I'm saying? So, I was just thinking about that.

00:25:32.776 --> 00:25:40.854
And I know what the Lord has shown me about certain investments like cryptos and things, and I thought, 'Lord, we just need the fountain.

00:25:40.855 --> 00:25:50.169
We need that to turn on for this end-time harvest.'You know, because I know what he's shown me, but I know what he said to me about Satan.

00:25:50.170 --> 00:26:09.479
This is Satan's wheelhouse, and he always talks to me about finances and how the devil tries to block it from the believers, tries to keep people poor, because if he can control the money, he can control stuff.

00:26:09.480 --> 00:26:14.116
He tries to put his hand in there and block stuff. And that's why we come as a believing believer.

00:26:14.117 --> 00:26:29.279
And I told the Lord, 'There's seed in the ground.'I know there's people out there that have sacrificially given, you all, to churches, to ministries, and you haven't seen your harvest yet.

00:26:29.280 --> 00:26:37.319
So, I start going, 'Lord, what's the holdup? Teach me, Father, so I can teach all these people.

00:26:37.320 --> 00:26:42.141
What's the holdup to these people's prosperity?'Because some people say, 'Well, it's a lack of faith, brother.

00:26:42.142 --> 00:26:45.039
You know, it's like you're always praying for healing, you never get your healing.

00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:55.919
Well, you know, it's because you might be living in sin, you might—well, it could be because you haven't spoken right.'And there's always some kind of Christian cliché of why you haven't got your breakthrough.

00:26:55.920 --> 00:27:16.171
'Well, it's because you're in strife with your wife, that's probably it.'And I go, 'But what if you're not, and you're still doing all there else to do is stand?'But I believe in speaking and calling those things that be not as though they were, and calling that money in.

00:27:16.172 --> 00:27:27.399
But I got so tired because I was raised this way, always believing for the mailbox mentality. 'Well, we need a miracle.

00:27:27.400 --> 00:27:41.222
Yep, Sister so-and-so, we didn't have money for food, so if Sister so-and-so doesn't give you the money, you don't have the money to get through the rest of the week.'But you live from miracle to miracle to miracle, but you don't live in overflow, but yet you sacrificially give.

00:27:41.223 --> 00:27:46.799
And I think, 'What is the holdup? Where is the break?'Where is this?

00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:50.649
So that's where I told Diana, oh, I got to take the blood. I apologize.

00:27:50.650 --> 00:27:57.039
I got on something because the Holy Spirit triggered me. I'm not going to lose this because this is going to help you.

00:27:57.040 --> 00:28:05.719
Father, I plead the blood of Jesus, and I apply the blood, and I thank you, Father, for the blood of Jesus right now.

00:28:05.720 --> 00:28:14.183
And we thank you, Lord, that it never loses its power. And I plead the blood of Jesus over this room, over me, my mind, my will, my emotions in Jesus'name.

00:28:14.184 --> 00:28:28.759
And we make much of the blood. Amen and amen. Now that's so much better than those little Dixie cup things. Okay.

00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:39.042
So I said I got so tired because I saw my mom and dad always sowing and struggling, and as a young man, I struggled myself when I first got married.

00:28:39.043 --> 00:28:46.980
We struggled really bad, and I got tired of it, living on food stamps, and you're sowing and you're giving.

00:28:46.981 --> 00:28:51.826
Like I said, we were required to tithe at our church. If we didn't tithe, we were fired.

00:28:51.827 --> 00:28:59.918
They would look at the register of who gave what, and if you were on staff and you didn't tithe a certain amount, they'd call you into the office and say, 'Where's the tithe?

00:28:59.919 --> 00:29:04.439
Where's your tithe at?'And I'd say, 'I didn't have it to give.

00:29:04.440 --> 00:29:10.479
We were trying to pay our electric.''Well, you know the rules. If you don't tithe, you don't work here.

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:18.079
Either you tithe and you give, or you're fired.'So we were forced to tithe.

00:29:18.080 --> 00:29:22.199
That's just the way it was. You tithed before you paid your bills.

00:29:22.200 --> 00:29:28.780
And if you didn't, you were fired working on staff at this mega-church I worked at. And so I had a real hard problem with that.

00:29:28.781 --> 00:29:35.839
And my heart really was cranky about it because my kids weren't doing without—we were living on food stamps and I was angry.

00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:43.319
But one day I gave it to God, and I said, 'God, either it's true or it's not.

00:29:43.320 --> 00:29:49.879
Either you're a blesser or this whole thing's a lie. But I refuse to live this way anymore.

00:29:49.880 --> 00:29:54.199
You either anoint my mind—I know I'm a man that doesn't have a lot of education.

00:29:54.200 --> 00:29:59.686
I know my wife is a beautiful woman to me, and she's suffering.

00:29:59.687 --> 00:30:04.627
We had to go to thrift stores to buy our kids'clothes, all our baby clothes, all of it.

00:30:04.628 --> 00:30:08.342
We only looked for stuff at garage sales for a quarter, ten cents.

00:30:08.343 --> 00:30:14.533
What could we do to haggle to be able to clothe our kids? And that's the way it was forever.

00:30:14.534 --> 00:30:18.095
That's the way even our bottles, whatever we could find, we bought everything at garage sales.

00:30:18.096 --> 00:30:25.999
We would go to the rich neighborhoods and we would take 20 bucks, and we'd buy our kids'fall clothes with it, or summer, or whatever we had.

00:30:26.000 --> 00:30:30.439
And we were excited if we could get it at Target because their clothes were better than Walmart's.

00:30:30.440 --> 00:30:38.242
And so this is the way it was. And so that's what I was trying to tell people.

00:30:38.243 --> 00:30:43.319
I came up with the idea to do eBay—well, Diana did, it wasn't me.

00:30:43.320 --> 00:30:48.097
I was praying in the spirit, praying in the spirit, and then one day she came to me.

00:30:48.098 --> 00:30:54.732
She said, 'Brandon, I have an idea.'And I thought she was nuts because we didn't have enough money to pay our electric bill.

00:30:54.733 --> 00:30:57.561
And she said, 'Bren, I'm going to take this last $100 we have.

00:30:57.562 --> 00:31:01.873
We don't have enough to pay the electric anyway, so they're going to cut it off in two weeks.

00:31:01.874 --> 00:31:09.399
So let's just take that $100 and do something with it, and try to make it happen.'And I looked at her and said, 'Are you nuts?

00:31:09.400 --> 00:31:24.331
I can try to scrounge up $100 more to pay our electric bill, and we won't have any food money or gas money, but at least our power will be on so we don't go without power.'She said, 'No, I feel this in my spirit.'I said, 'Whatever you feel, hun, I'll back it.'So that's where it started from.

00:31:24.332 --> 00:31:36.672
But he got so tired of sowing in the offering and waiting for a miracle always, and instead he said, 'Whatever you do, I'll give you power to get wealth.

00:31:36.673 --> 00:31:50.515
You go out and make it happen, Captain. Stop waiting for a handout.'It's like this, you know, when people say, 'Teach a person to fish.

00:31:50.516 --> 00:31:57.712
If you give somebody a fish, they'll have enough for a day. If you teach a person to fish, they'll be able to feed themselves forever,'you know, kind of a deal.

00:31:57.713 --> 00:32:11.854
I probably butchered that, but it's similar. But I'm trying to tell you all, out of desperation, doing eBay, Poshmark, and Mercari changed our life.

00:32:11.855 --> 00:32:23.359
But we didn't wait for it to happen; we went out and took what's ours. We learned to go to thrift stores. It took us forever.

00:32:23.360 --> 00:32:32.479
Diana and me, praying in the spirit for hours and hours—that's where I learned to develop my gift.

00:32:32.480 --> 00:32:42.709
But it was out of desperation, and I would learn where to go, asking the Father, 'Show me where the good stuff is.

00:32:42.710 --> 00:32:54.719
I'm looking for something that sells for more.'So, just praying in the spirit, and eBay changed our life. The Holy Spirit used that to change our life.

00:32:54.720 --> 00:33:04.599
And it was to the point where, in the first six months, we made more money than we made an entire year at the church.

00:33:04.600 --> 00:33:08.661
And it started compounding. We just kept growing and kept doing it.

00:33:08.662 --> 00:33:14.678
But I want to tell you, I got so tired of the—wow, I wonder what that's all about.

00:33:14.679 --> 00:33:25.959
You hear those, please. I got so tired of the prosperity preaching at church.

00:33:25.960 --> 00:33:38.519
A lot of charismatic, 'Sow your $58 seed'—not that I'm knocking that, man—'Sow your 58 for your $58 miracle.'I'm very careful; I don't touch the anointing.

00:33:38.520 --> 00:33:45.359
But I got tired of hearing it and not seeing the fruit of it, and always not putting my boat into motion.

00:33:45.360 --> 00:33:52.162
And so I tell you all this because I think it gets real flaky there. There's a real flakiness to it.

00:33:52.163 --> 00:34:10.639
I asked God, 'Show me how to flip a car.'So I'd find a car that was on another part of town, try to find it for a cheap deal—800 bucks—and try to flip it.

00:34:10.640 --> 00:34:16.717
Put a little bit of money—it might be a clunker that's broken—put a little bit of money into it, clean it up real good, put some new tires on it.

00:34:16.718 --> 00:34:21.238
Maybe they're used, because I always look for used tires. You can find some tires that were not too treaded out.

00:34:21.239 --> 00:34:34.878
I don't know why I'm telling you, but there's some for somebody trying to figure out how to double and triple your money, asking the Holy Spirit to give you wisdom about it, do you know what I'm saying?

00:34:34.879 --> 00:34:41.479
Not waiting for somebody always to hand you a Holy Ghost handshake.

00:34:41.480 --> 00:34:57.839
'Here, brother, here's your $100.'You're going, 'Oh my God, thank God I got $100, that'll get me through two days.'And you're going, 'Oh God, I've got to believe for the next one.'But believing God for so much more than always just waiting for your Holy Ghost handshake at church.

00:34:57.840 --> 00:35:03.297
You know what I'm talking about—Holy Ghost handshake. You're looking for a sister with a lot of money. And a lot of times you see the ministry of hints.

00:35:03.298 --> 00:35:17.279
You're walking around going, 'Well, I'm believing God for my electric bill today,'and you're talking to the rich people at church, hoping they'll have sympathy on you, that they'll want to help pay your electric bill because you're going, 'Oh God, you know, we've been struggling.

00:35:17.280 --> 00:35:22.550
You know, we're believing God just like everybody.'And you look at them, they're going, 'Okay, well, I know what you're doing.

00:35:22.551 --> 00:35:29.079
You're asking for money in a polite Christianese way.'I didn't want to be that.

00:35:29.080 --> 00:35:41.919
I wanted to be the man with a picture in his hand. Teach me. Teach me to not fish with just a fishing pole. Teach me to fish with a net, Father. Teach me.

00:35:41.920 --> 00:35:58.839
And that's why I continually am asking the Father, and when I hear about Magdala and these projects—and I think it's like $20 million to finish this project, it's huge money, right?—and I go, 'That should not be.

00:35:58.840 --> 00:36:12.957
The body of Christ should be the head, not the tail, above and not beneath.'But I think a lot of the times because it is Satan's wheelhouse, and he tries to block the blessing from the body of Christ so much because he knows what it's going to take to get the gospel out, because why?

00:36:12.958 --> 00:36:21.759
It's all about souls. The more we have the money, the more we have the finances, we're able to get the job done so we can get out of here.

00:36:21.760 --> 00:36:26.737
But if you're broke, you can't even give enough. It's like the youth project at the church trying to finish the rest of that.

00:36:26.738 --> 00:36:31.919
I think they need another, like, $200,000 or something more.

00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:37.159
So, if you're in a small community, $200,000 is a lot of money. Do you get that?

00:36:37.160 --> 00:36:43.642
So you get a little bit here, you get a little bit there, and you're excited whenever you get enough to be able to put some cement slabs up or whatever.

00:36:43.643 --> 00:36:55.761
But I thought, what does it take to be a paymaster? What does it take to be that person that has the big money, like the Greens?

00:36:55.762 --> 00:37:02.743
If it wasn't for the Greens of Hobby Lobby, ORU wouldn't exist right now. The Holy Spirit used them.

00:37:02.744 --> 00:37:08.348
And some people get ticked off at people being, you know, they say, 'F the rich'and all this craziness, whatever.

00:37:08.349 --> 00:37:17.730
I mean, it's so ignorant. If it wasn't for the Greens being used by the Holy Spirit, ORU would have closed their doors.

00:37:17.731 --> 00:37:24.639
I think they had to give them $47 million or they would have closed their doors because of mismanagement of money.

00:37:24.640 --> 00:37:31.924
There had to be something, but it was them bailing them out that God used to help save that whole university.

00:37:31.925 --> 00:37:37.639
And my wife graduated there, thank God. Thank God, it is a Christian university.

00:37:37.640 --> 00:37:42.999
They're changing lives. But the Lord showed me a major revival is about to happen there.

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:57.439
But it took somebody with some common sense that had 400 stores, Hobby Lobbies, and Mardel's all throughout the United States that was able to say, 'Here, here's a $47 million check.'I don't know about you, but even a million-dollar check, I'd pass out.

00:37:57.440 --> 00:38:09.169
$100,000, you know, come on. But 47 million bucks here, do you—that is an absurd amount of money.

00:38:09.170 --> 00:38:15.790
That's crazy money. But they had it, and I thought we need more people like that.

00:38:15.791 --> 00:38:20.316
But what is it going to take to get that? First, the love of money is the root of all evil.

00:38:20.317 --> 00:38:24.439
If you're crazy about money and God can't get it through you, He won't get it to you.

00:38:24.440 --> 00:38:33.769
So, I really truly believe there's something more to this for the end-time harvest and the end-time wealth transfer for what we need for these next couple of months and going into the next year.

00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:38.810
I heard one pastor talking about how we're about to have an economic crisis.

00:38:38.811 --> 00:38:46.639
I believe there's an outpouring of finances first. And that's what I believe for the body of Christ, that we lack nothing.

00:38:46.640 --> 00:38:52.919
We should not be lacking anything. We need this to get the job done.

00:38:52.920 --> 00:38:57.809
So, I think about things all the time. I pray and the Lord gives me these ideas.

00:38:57.810 --> 00:39:01.625
I'm driving down the road and He'll say, 'That land over there.

00:39:01.626 --> 00:39:12.835
If somebody buys that, they'll be able to, and within the next couple of months, that land's going to quadruple in price and it'd be worth millions.'But that takes money to buy that.

00:39:12.836 --> 00:39:19.633
But He's always educating me. He's always teaching me about the end-time harvest money.

00:39:19.634 --> 00:39:24.522
He teaches me all the time and He talks to me, and I know something's about to happen.

00:39:24.523 --> 00:39:28.350
I know. I just believe it because I'm like, 'Why are you telling me this stuff?

00:39:28.351 --> 00:39:32.930
Are you just educating me?'Practicing His presence—people go, 'What's that mean, Brandon?

00:39:32.931 --> 00:39:40.358
What does that mean to practice His presence?'Act like He's there.

00:39:40.359 --> 00:39:46.800
I don't look at God as twinkle, twinkle, little star. 'Lord, you're way out there somewhere where you are.'He's in me.

00:39:46.801 --> 00:39:59.272
He dwells. As He is, so are we in this world. I act like He's just like my wife sitting next to me. 'Hey, how's your day? I love you. I want to talk to you.

00:39:59.273 --> 00:40:07.159
Are you my friend?'When I told you I ticked Him off yesterday, I knew it immediately because my broadcast was terrible.

00:40:07.160 --> 00:40:18.205
And I said, 'Lord, why is this so bad?'He said, 'Your attitude's bad, and I'm not going to pour that cloak on you. It's teaching you. You cannot have that.

00:40:18.206 --> 00:40:38.679
You've got to repent and go on.'And the moment I fixed it—but it caused me to align because, bottom line, folks, I was irritated because there were so many of you all irritated that came to the meeting that wanted to talk to me and I didn't know how to handle it, and there were things that I had to deal with in my heart about it.

00:40:38.680 --> 00:40:43.479
And the Lord instructed me because I didn't know what to do. I'm new at this.

00:40:43.480 --> 00:40:52.020
I'm just a dude that's just getting raised up in ministry, and I'm just telling you all, I don't have all the answers and I'm asking the Holy Spirit, 'You teach me.

00:40:52.021 --> 00:41:00.519
I need you. I don't know what to do.'And as I grow, and I've seen my elders, you know, that have been in this for 50 years...

00:41:00.520 --> 00:41:07.440
like a widow woman. She was a widow raising up four kids by herself without a husband.

00:41:07.441 --> 00:41:17.448
He died at 48 years old, 49 years old, and she raised kids up all that rest of that time by herself and had them and everything, and God used her.

00:41:17.449 --> 00:41:21.424
And she carried a ministry without a husband all those years.

00:41:21.425 --> 00:41:25.561
And there's something to learn about that. That's honorable.

00:41:25.562 --> 00:41:32.186
I can't imagine, usually, a woman doing something by herself without a husband back there beside her to help do it.

00:41:32.188 --> 00:41:35.886
I know Kathryn Kuhlman did some things, but she was married at some point in time.

00:41:35.887 --> 00:41:41.473
But there's something to be said about that. Longevity in ministry is not an easy thing.

00:41:41.474 --> 00:41:46.594
I've seen them come and I've seen them go. You see a spark and you go, 'What happened to them?

00:41:46.595 --> 00:41:56.713
There was an anointing on them one time, but they're gone.'But when you say, 'I've been in ministry and I'm a female and I've been doing this for 40, 50 years, whatever.

00:41:56.714 --> 00:42:05.359
How long has yours been?'you should pay attention because they're doing something where they beat the odds.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:09.519
It's like you watch somebody and they've played chess perfectly.

00:42:09.520 --> 00:42:18.999
'How did you do that?'Only by the grace of God, by the glory of God. That's not normal. If it was, everybody would do it.

00:42:19.000 --> 00:42:25.483
But God puts His hand on people and you honor it and you learn from it. I've learned to be quiet and listen.

00:42:25.484 --> 00:42:39.319
I may talk a lot sometimes around them because I'm trying to pull stuff from them, but I'm learning to be still and listen because you can learn a lot more with these two ears than always with your mouth.

00:42:39.320 --> 00:42:46.599
It's the truth. I listen to them and I go, 'There's something so deep.'I know they don't talk a lot.

00:42:46.600 --> 00:42:50.393
These elders don't talk a lot. They don't. So, I pull from them.

00:42:50.394 --> 00:42:55.957
I try to grasp wisdom when I get these conversations with them, the more I get into ministry, because I want to learn.

00:42:55.958 --> 00:43:00.689
I don't want to learn from the young buck. I want to learn from the old one because they're still alive.

00:43:00.690 --> 00:43:09.802
It's the old deer with the old antlers that's made it through all the hunting seasons that you go, 'How did you make it?'The young buck, he's just dodged some arrows.

00:43:09.803 --> 00:43:13.500
He's dodged some bullets and he's still going, saying, 'I've made it.'And you're like, 'Sit down, buddy.

00:43:13.501 --> 00:43:20.759
You don't know nothing.'But it's the old deer that the meat's tough, and you go, 'How did you make it through all those hunting seasons?

00:43:20.760 --> 00:43:32.839
How did you do that?'It was by the grace of God. There's something about listening to the elders, and I honor it and I respect it so much.

00:43:32.840 --> 00:43:38.984
That's why I try to glean from Billy, both Billies. I go, 'Just give me five minutes of your time.

00:43:38.985 --> 00:43:45.403
Just—I want to know.'Especially if you see the anointing and you sense it there.

00:43:45.404 --> 00:43:48.526
You see people all the time, they lay hands on people, there ain't no power.

00:43:48.528 --> 00:44:01.319
But when you get around some people who have some power, 'Teach me how you got that spark and how it lasted.'They don't go around looking for everybody to lay hands on them.

00:44:01.320 --> 00:44:18.636
They got it and they know how to cultivate it themselves. And I go, 'That's it.'It's easy to get it and have it for a little bit, but to keep it and sustain it for decades, I don't know.

00:44:18.637 --> 00:44:21.199
I just tell you all my little things that I'm thinking about.

00:44:21.200 --> 00:44:29.159
That's my thing before I pray. I try to pull you along my road that I'm going down. I'm just really open and honest with y'all.

00:44:29.160 --> 00:44:51.999
You know, I don't have it all figured out, but I watch the elders and I watch the people and I listen to their conversations, and I think about what they think about going on because I know what the Father has told me I'm going to do and I don't have a clue how I'm going to get there.

00:44:52.000 --> 00:45:00.199
In fact, it freaks me out. It freaks Diana out, and I go, "It'll only be by the grace."All what I'm doing right now is all God.

00:45:00.200 --> 00:45:06.971
It's not that I'm a polished speaker. It's not that I have some kind of something special.

00:45:06.972 --> 00:45:14.959
He showed me something, and the cloak comes on, and I tell you what's coming because he says to do it, and I pray it lasts.

00:45:14.960 --> 00:45:24.879
I just say, "Okay, God."But if it don't, I act like yesterday: I pull the video, I turn it off, and I say, "We're going on our way,"because it was stinky.

00:45:24.880 --> 00:45:36.846
There was no anointing. I feel his presence right now. That's why I keep talking. I feel him. I feel him.

00:45:36.847 --> 00:45:49.789
And when I feel him, I go, "Oh, in his presence there's fullness of joy."And there's so many people that I've come across, even at this meeting, that are so desperate for so much.

00:45:49.790 --> 00:45:57.432
It's like this one man came up to me: "I'm not letting you go until you give me my blessing."I don't know what to give.

00:45:57.433 --> 00:46:03.316
I don't have nothing for you. I don't know what to even tell you.

00:46:03.317 --> 00:46:11.919
But so many people are so desperate. So this is my time to tell you we're in the end times. We're here.

00:46:11.920 --> 00:46:24.639
And it's amazing to be able to talk to another seer tonight that is seeing, and has contacts with the government, and is able to say, "Listen, Brandon, you're right on target.

00:46:24.640 --> 00:46:57.079
All glory to Jesus."So, I've had some amazing prophetic words, and they give you hope to keep you going, to tell you this is what God's called you to do and this is what you're going to do, and it's going to be so all this and all that, and you go, "Okay, God, you know, but I just trust you, but I need impartation."And I go, and I seek it, and I get it, and I grab a hold of it like a bulldog on a bone.

00:46:57.080 --> 00:47:06.742
And I'm saying, "I'm going to fight and contend for what's mine, what God has for me so I can give it to the people, so that when I get on the other side, he says, 'Well done, thou good and faithful servant.

00:47:06.743 --> 00:47:18.733
